f=Engineering/nova/custom/app-store-release-discipline/SKILL.md · in=app-store-release-discipline nova's shipping law, differs web one brutal way: **you can't instantly roll back mobile release.** bad web deploy reverted seconds (ops); bad app-store release already users' phones fix through store review again. mobile shipping staged-rollout-first, review-guideline-aware, even conservative web rollback ops relies barely exists here. · p=Mobile release failures uniquely painful: crash ships millions, fix takes review cycle (hours days), users who auto-updated stuck. discipline front-loads caution: thorough pre-submission verification, staged rollout catch problems 100%, forward-fix readiness because backward-rollback weak. · wu=Triggers (only `mobile_active`): "release app," "submit store," "app store review," "staged rollout," "the app crashed production," any mobile release. · st:/ Protocol=`[GATE: mobile_active?] A mobile release candidate \· -> PRE-SUBMISSION: quinn gate + mobile-verification on real devices (both OSes) + charter clean \· -> STORE GUIDELINES: review-guideline compliance checked (rejection = lost days) \· -> VERSIONING: build/version bumped correctly; release notes; phased-release configured \· -> STAGED ROLLOUT: 1% → 10% → 100%, watching crash-free rate + reviews at each stage` · in=**Check switch.** `mobile_active` false dormant. app, releases. **Verify real devices before submission.** quinn's gate plus mobile-verification actual iOS Android devices simulator lies about performance, permissions, device-specific bugs. crash found post-submission costs review cycle. **Know store guidelines.** iOS Android review guidelines reject specific reasons (privacy labels, permissions justification, payment rules); non-compliance lost days, minutes. dated playbook tracks current guideline specifics. **Staged rollout rollback.** Release 1%, 10%, 100%, watching crash-free rate review sentiment gate. mobile's answer ops's instant rollback you can't pull back, you catch small. Halt rollout moment metrics degrade. **Forward-fix readiness.** Because rollback weak (users bad build), keep ability ship fix fast feature flags disable broken feature server-side without new release (raj/service-patterns), expedited-review readiness severe cases. **The operator holds signing secrets.** App signing keys/certs held used operator, agent mobile analogue charter's don't-hold-secrets stance; leaked signing key catastrophic. · of=`## App Release: [version] — [mobile_active ✓] \· Pre-submission: quinn gate [ref] \· real-device verify (iOS+Android) ✓ \· charter clean \· Store guidelines: [compliant ✓ / risks] \· Version/notes: [ ] \· Phased release: [configured] \· Staged rollout: 1% → 10% → 100% — crash-free rate + reviews watched at each \· Rollback reality: [forward-fix ready \· feature-flag kill-switch \· expedited review if severe]` · pr=**You can't instantly roll back mobile** staged rollout rollback; catch small., **Real-device verify before submission** simulator lies; post-submission crash costs review cycle., **Store-guideline compliance** rejection lost days., **Forward-fix readiness** feature-flag kill-switches expedited review, because backward-rollback weak., **The operator holds signing secrets** leaked signing key catastrophic., **More conservative web** safety net (instant rollback) barely exists. · f=`mobile_active` false → dormant., phased-release support (some contexts) smaller test cohorts (TestFlight/internal track) first, full approximate staged rollout., Severe bug already 100% forward-fix expedited review server-side feature-flag disable (raj) immediate mitigation; flag what saves you rollback can't. · b:with Other Skills=**ops/release-discipline**: web analogue; mobile counterpart, conservative because rollback weak. Coordinate cadence., **mobile-verification** (sibling): real-device testing pass before submission., **mobile-app-architecture** (sibling) dated playbook: build/signing mechanics., **raj/service-patterns**: server-side feature flags kill-switch bad build ships (the real mobile safety net)., **quinn**: gate precedes submission; **aegis**: privacy/permissions/signing security surfaces.